<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The statement "(void) cls;" is a no-op used to suppress an unused-parameter warning. It performs no observable action and removing it would not affect program behaviour, so it is an executed operation whose removal has no effect — i.e. dead code. Therefore Rule 2.2 is violated (the same applies to the similar "(void) connection;" and "(void) toe;" lines).
</scenario>
